cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a method for reducing the computational complexity of deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves pruning feature maps and kernels, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the method, which could fall under the category of computer systems (cs.DS).
